remble at the ferocity of the believers in deep and rigid abstraction. Feel the pain as you work with our young heroine, Emmy Germain, as she blazes a trail for women in mathematical research and learns from Professor Gauss, the greatest forensic detective of them all.Beautifully drawn and wittily and exquisitely detailed, Prime Suspects is unique, astonishing, and outrageous-a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to experience mathematics like never before.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aMathematicsvComic books, strips, etc. 0aMurderxInvestigationvComic books, strips, etc. 7aMATHEMATICS / Number Theory.2bisacsh1 aGauss, K. F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGranville, Jennifer, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSchneider, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2019 Englishz978311061040608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2019z9783110606362oZDB-23-DMA40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691188737zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691188737423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691188737.jpg  a978-3-11-061040-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DMAb201